window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Influenced by Vonnegut, Jose Saramago, David Foster Wallace, Will Ferguson, Lynn Coady, and the Coen Brothers, Buddy Roy Baldry inhabits the wildlands of Canada, where he writes darkly humorous novels about the everyday human neurosis of ordinary people in extraordinary situations.</p> <p>Whether drug dealer, or cop, doctor, or insurance salesman, it seems everyone wants something else for their lives; an escape from who they are. A chance to become who they feel they should have always been. Larry Hansen is among them, but he is not the only one.</p> <p>Some may succeed, many will fail. If escape is on your mind, are you running to something, or running from something?</p>"; 
